ciscoWanAtmCosbMIB.name: ciscoWanAtmCosbMIB

revisions.description: Descriptions have been clarified for few objects or tables.

1. Added following objects to cwacIntervalTable, as upper 32-bits for counters which are 64-bit wide: cwacHighIntCellArrivals, cwacHighIntCellDiscards, cwacHighIntCellDeparts. 2. Added following 64-bit objects to cwacIntervalTable for 64-bit counter support: cwacHCIntCellArrivals, cwacHCIntCellDiscards, cwacHCIntCellDeparts
Initial version of this MIB module.

ciscoWanAtmCosbMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-wanatm@cisco.com
ciscoWanAtmCosbMIB.description: The MIB to manage CoS(Class of Service) queue/buffer related parameters. One or more virtual interfaces may exist on a physical interface or a channelized interface. Every virtual interface has certain number (e.g. 16) of CoS queues. These queues are also known as Class Of Service Buffers. Every COS queue maps to an ATM trafiic type such as CBR, VBR-rt, ABR etc. These COS queues are used to provide QOS (quality of service), depending on the corresponding ATM trafiic type. This MIB provides management functionality such as Threshold Crossing Alarms(TCA) for cell discards and interval statistics for these COS queues.

cwacStatsAlarmConfgTable.name: cwacStatsAlarmConfgTable
cwacStatsAlarmConfgTable.description: This table contains alarm configuration parameters related to CoS queue. Entries in this table are automatically created when a new virtual interface is added.

cwacStatsAlarmConfgEntry.name: cwacStatsAlarmConfgEntry
cwacStatsAlarmConfgEntry.description: An entry in CoS queue alarm configuration table. This table is indexed by ifIndex, that belongs to the ifTable entry with ifType value atmVirtual(149), and cwacCosbIndex.

cwacCosbIndex.name: cwacCosbIndex
cwacCosbIndex.description: This is the CoS queue number to which this entry belongs.

cwacCosbCurrentCellsDiscThres.name: cwacCosbCurrentCellsDiscThres
cwacCosbCurrentCellsDiscThres.description: This object indicates the threshold for cell discards for the current 15-min interval, above which alarm is generated.

cwacStatsAlarmStatus.name: cwacStatsAlarmStatus
cwacStatsAlarmStatus.description: This is a bitmap that shows the status of TCA(Threshold Crossing Alarm) of current queue. This bitmap is sent as part of the trap that is generated as part of TCA being raised. Bit assignmed is as follows: ---------------------------- 1 Cell discard 15 minute threshold was exceeded.

cwacValidIntervals.name: cwacValidIntervals
cwacValidIntervals.description: The number of previous intervals for which valid data has been stored.

cwacIntervalTable.name: cwacIntervalTable
cwacIntervalTable.description: This table reflects interval statistics associated with each of the CoS queues. Entries in this table are automatically created when a new virtual interface is added.

cwacIntervalEntry.name: cwacIntervalEntry
cwacIntervalEntry.description: An entry for per virtual interface CoS queue interval statistics. In addition to the current 15-minute interval bucket, the previous 24 hours worth of 15-minute interval buckets are collected for each vitual interface. This table is indexed by ifIndex, that belongs to the ifTable entry with ifType value atmVirtual(149), cwacCosbIndex and cwacIntervalNumber.

cwacIntervalNumber.name: cwacIntervalNumber
cwacIntervalNumber.description: A number used to uniquely identify per virtual interface CoS queue interval statistics. 0 is used to identify the current 15-minute interval. 1-96 identify the previous 24 hours of 15-minute interval buckets.

cwacIntCellArrivals.name: cwacIntCellArrivals
cwacIntCellArrivals.description: The number of cells arrived at the queue during a particular 15 minute interval.

cwacIntCellDiscards.name: cwacIntCellDiscards
cwacIntCellDiscards.description: The number of cells discarded due to congestion during a particular 15 minute interval.

cwacIntCellDeparts.name: cwacIntCellDeparts
cwacIntCellDeparts.description: The number of cells that left the QBIN during a particular 15 minute interval.

cwacHighIntCellArrivals.name: cwacHighIntCellArrivals
cwacHighIntCellArrivals.description: The upper 32-bits of the number of cells arrived at the queue during a particular 15-minute interval.

cwacHighIntCellDiscards.name: cwacHighIntCellDiscards
cwacHighIntCellDiscards.description: The upper 32-bits of the number of cells discarded due to congestion during a particular 15-minute interval.

cwacHighIntCellDeparts.name: cwacHighIntCellDeparts
cwacHighIntCellDeparts.description: The upper 32-bits of the number of cells that left the QBIN during a particular 15-minute interval.

cwacHCIntCellArrivals.name: cwacHCIntCellArrivals
cwacHCIntCellArrivals.description: The 64 bit value of the number of cells arriving at the queue during a particular 15-minute interval.

cwacHCIntCellDiscards.name: cwacHCIntCellDiscards
cwacHCIntCellDiscards.description: The 64 bit value of the number of cells discarded due to congestion during a particular 15-minute interval.

cwacHCIntCellDeparts.name: cwacHCIntCellDeparts
cwacHCIntCellDeparts.description: The 64 bit value of the number of cells that left the QBIN during a particular 15-minute interval.

ciscoWanAtmCosbAlarmMIBGroup.description: The statistical per virtual interface CoS queue alarm group.
